Gov. Aminu Tambuwal of Sokoto State on Tuesday approved the appointment of Alhaji Umar Dodo, as the substantive clerk to the state House of Assembly. Tambuwal said in Sokoto that the appointment was in line with the law establishing the state House of Assembly Service Commission. He said that a letter to that effect had been communicated to the new clerk. The News men reports that Dodoâ€™s appointment followed the demise of the former clerk, Alhaji Sulaiman Muhammad, who died on May 29, 2017 Dodo was the Deputy Clerk to the assembly before his elevation. NAN